{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":586,"text":"I'm going to talk a little bit about strategy"},{"time":2649,"text":"and its relationship with technology."},{"time":6823,"text":"We tend to think of business strategy"},{"time":9718,"text":"as being a rather abstract body"},{"time":11681,"text":"of essentially economic thought,"},{"time":13396,"text":"perhaps rather timeless."},{"time":15026,"text":"I'm going to argue that, in fact,"},{"time":16966,"text":"business strategy has always been premised"},{"time":19521,"text":"on assumptions about technology,"},{"time":21940,"text":"that those assumptions are changing,"},{"time":23913,"text":"and, in fact, changing quite dramatically,"},{"time":26630,"text":"and that therefore what that will drive us to"},{"time":29702,"text":"is a different concept of what we mean"},{"time":32605,"text":"by business strategy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":35043,"text":"Let me start, if I may,"},{"time":36524,"text":"with a little bit of history."},{"time":39294,"text":"The idea of strategy in business"},{"time":41038,"text":"owes its origins to two intellectual giants:"},{"time":44338,"text":"Bruce Henderson, the founder of BCG,"},{"time":46472,"text":"and Michael Porter, professor\nat the Harvard Business School."},{"time":50244,"text":"Henderson's central idea was what you might call"},{"time":53076,"text":"the Napoleonic idea of concentrating mass"},{"time":56067,"text":"against weakness, of overwhelming the enemy."},{"time":58936,"text":"What Henderson recognized was that,"},{"time":60729,"text":"in the business world,"},{"time":62125,"text":"there are many phenomena which are characterized"},{"time":64780,"text":"by what economists would call increasing returns --"},{"time":66815,"text":"scale, experience."},{"time":68178,"text":"The more you do of something,"},{"time":70052,"text":"disproportionately the better you get."},{"time":72449,"text":"And therefore he found a logic for investing"},{"time":75412,"text":"in such kinds of overwhelming mass"},{"time":78154,"text":"in order to achieve competitive advantage."},{"time":80707,"text":"And that was the first introduction"},{"time":82775,"text":"of essentially a military concept of strategy"},{"time":85439,"text":"into the business world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":88421,"text":"Porter agreed with that premise,"},{"time":91156,"text":"but he qualified it."},{"time":92707,"text":"He pointed out, correctly, that that's all very well,"},{"time":95696,"text":"but businesses actually have multiple steps to them."},{"time":99571,"text":"They have different components,"},{"time":101144,"text":"and each of those components might be driven"},{"time":103676,"text":"by a different kind of strategy."},{"time":105461,"text":"A company or a business\nmight actually be advantaged"},{"time":107789,"text":"in some activities but disadvantaged in others."},{"time":111267,"text":"He formed the concept of the value chain,"},{"time":113368,"text":"essentially the sequence of steps with which"},{"time":116438,"text":"a, shall we say, raw material, becomes a component,"},{"time":119590,"text":"becomes assembled into a finished product,"},{"time":120953,"text":"and then is distributed, for example,"},{"time":123594,"text":"and he argued that advantage accrued"},{"time":126010,"text":"to each of those components,"},{"time":127551,"text":"and that the advantage of the whole"},{"time":129265,"text":"was in some sense the sum or the average"},{"time":131396,"text":"of that of its parts."},{"time":133744,"text":"And this idea of the value chain was predicated"},{"time":136321,"text":"on the recognition that"},{"time":138889,"text":"what holds a business together is transaction costs,"},{"time":142535,"text":"that in essence you need to coordinate,"},{"time":144830,"text":"organizations are more efficient at coordination"},{"time":147405,"text":"than markets, very often,"},{"time":149067,"text":"and therefore the nature and role and boundaries"},{"time":152123,"text":"of the cooperation are defined by transaction costs."},{"time":155962,"text":"It was on those two ideas,"},{"time":158526,"text":"Henderson's idea of increasing returns"},{"time":161912,"text":"to scale and experience,"},{"time":163460,"text":"and Porter's idea of the value chain,"},{"time":165883,"text":"encompassing heterogenous elements,"},{"time":167796,"text":"that the whole edifice of business strategy"},{"time":171131,"text":"was subsequently erected."}]},{"cues":[{"time":173908,"text":"Now what I'm going to argue is"},{"time":176337,"text":"that those premises are, in fact, being invalidated."},{"time":182051,"text":"First of all, let's think about transaction costs."},{"time":184605,"text":"There are really two components\nto transaction costs."},{"time":187002,"text":"One is about processing information,\nand the other is about communication."},{"time":189872,"text":"These are the economics of\nprocessing and communicating"},{"time":193153,"text":"as they have evolved over a long period of time."},{"time":195627,"text":"As we all know from so many contexts,"},{"time":198637,"text":"they have been radically transformed"},{"time":200893,"text":"since the days when Porter and Henderson"},{"time":203205,"text":"first formulated their theories."},{"time":205299,"text":"In particular, since the mid-'90s,"},{"time":207365,"text":"communications costs have actually been falling"},{"time":209233,"text":"even faster than transaction costs,"},{"time":211224,"text":"which is why communication, the Internet,"},{"time":213783,"text":"has exploded in such a dramatic fashion."},{"time":218398,"text":"Now, those falling transaction costs"},{"time":220568,"text":"have profound consequences,"},{"time":222544,"text":"because if transaction costs are the glue"},{"time":224337,"text":"that hold value chains together, and they are falling,"},{"time":226759,"text":"there is less to economize on."},{"time":228401,"text":"There is less need for vertically\nintegrated organization,"},{"time":231333,"text":"and value chains at least can break up."},{"time":234211,"text":"They needn't necessarily, but they can."},{"time":236710,"text":"In particular, it then becomes possible for"},{"time":238850,"text":"a competitor in one business"},{"time":240616,"text":"to use their position in one step of the value chain"},{"time":243941,"text":"in order to penetrate or attack"},{"time":245773,"text":"or disintermediate the competitor in another."}]},{"cues":[{"time":248937,"text":"That is not just an abstract proposition."},{"time":251598,"text":"There are many very specific stories"},{"time":253277,"text":"of how that actually happened."},{"time":255049,"text":"A poster child example was\nthe encyclopedia business."},{"time":258542,"text":"The encyclopedia business"},{"time":259991,"text":"in the days of leatherbound books"},{"time":262093,"text":"was basically a distribution business."},{"time":263797,"text":"Most of the cost was the\ncommission to the salesmen."},{"time":266251,"text":"The CD-ROM and then the Internet came along,"},{"time":268877,"text":"new technologies made the distribution of knowledge"},{"time":272293,"text":"many orders of magnitude cheaper,"},{"time":274572,"text":"and the encyclopedia industry collapsed."},{"time":277286,"text":"It's now, of course, a very familiar story."},{"time":280118,"text":"This, in fact, more generally was the story"},{"time":282160,"text":"of the first generation of the Internet economy."},{"time":284669,"text":"It was about falling transaction costs"},{"time":286869,"text":"breaking up value chains"},{"time":288344,"text":"and therefore allowing disintermediation,"},{"time":290973,"text":"or what we call deconstruction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":293310,"text":"One of the questions I was occasionally asked was,"},{"time":295627,"text":"well, what's going to replace the encyclopedia"},{"time":298143,"text":"when Britannica no longer has a business model?"},{"time":300794,"text":"And it was a while before\nthe answer became manifest."},{"time":302960,"text":"Now, of course, we know\nwhat it is: it's the Wikipedia."},{"time":305747,"text":"Now what's special about the\nWikipedia is not its distribution."},{"time":308970,"text":"What's special about the Wikipedia\nis the way it's produced."},{"time":311374,"text":"The Wikipedia, of course, is an encyclopedia"},{"time":313614,"text":"created by its users."},{"time":316141,"text":"And this, in fact, defines what you might call"},{"time":318021,"text":"the second decade of the Internet economy,"},{"time":320509,"text":"the decade in which the Internet as a noun"},{"time":323869,"text":"became the Internet as a verb."},{"time":325776,"text":"It became a set of conversations,"},{"time":327645,"text":"the era in which user-generated\ncontent and social networks"},{"time":331721,"text":"became the dominant phenomenon."},{"time":334412,"text":"Now what that really meant"},{"time":336310,"text":"in terms of the Porter-Henderson framework"},{"time":339684,"text":"was the collapse of certain\nkinds of economies of scale."},{"time":343075,"text":"It turned out that tens of thousands"},{"time":345413,"text":"of autonomous individuals writing an encyclopedia"},{"time":348496,"text":"could do just as good a job,"},{"time":350042,"text":"and certainly a much cheaper job,"},{"time":351733,"text":"than professionals in a hierarchical organization."},{"time":354712,"text":"So basically what was happening was that one layer"},{"time":357169,"text":"of this value chain was becoming fragmented,"},{"time":360063,"text":"as individuals could take over"},{"time":361907,"text":"where organizations were no longer needed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":365194,"text":"But there's another question\nthat obviously this graph poses,"},{"time":367826,"text":"which is, okay, we've\ngone through two decades --"},{"time":370109,"text":"does anything distinguish the third?"},{"time":372787,"text":"And what I'm going to argue is that indeed"},{"time":374902,"text":"something does distinguish the third,"},{"time":376407,"text":"and it maps exactly on to the kind of"},{"time":378853,"text":"Porter-Henderson logic that\nwe've been talking about."},{"time":381321,"text":"And that is, about data."},{"time":383908,"text":"If we go back to around 2000,"},{"time":385577,"text":"a lot of people were talking\nabout the information revolution,"},{"time":387936,"text":"and it was indeed true that the world's stock of data"},{"time":390237,"text":"was growing, indeed growing quite fast."},{"time":392511,"text":"but it was still at that point overwhelmingly analog."},{"time":395369,"text":"We go forward to 2007,"},{"time":397187,"text":"not only had the world's stock of data exploded,"},{"time":400372,"text":"but there'd been this massive substitution"},{"time":402892,"text":"of digital for analog."},{"time":404907,"text":"And more important even than that,"},{"time":406776,"text":"if you look more carefully at this graph,"},{"time":408516,"text":"what you will observe is that about a half"},{"time":410536,"text":"of that digital data"},{"time":412150,"text":"is information that has an I.P. address."},{"time":414536,"text":"It's on a server or it's on a P.C."},{"time":417387,"text":"But having an I.P. address means that it"},{"time":419194,"text":"can be connected to any other data"},{"time":421364,"text":"that has an I.P. address."},{"time":423227,"text":"It means it becomes possible"},{"time":424873,"text":"to put together half of the world's knowledge"},{"time":427960,"text":"in order to see patterns,"},{"time":429612,"text":"an entirely new thing."},{"time":431969,"text":"If we run the numbers forward to today,"},{"time":433937,"text":"it probably looks something like this."},{"time":435363,"text":"We're not really sure."},{"time":436531,"text":"If we run the numbers forward to 2020,"},{"time":438559,"text":"we of course have an exact number, courtesy of IDC."},{"time":441459,"text":"It's curious that the future is so much\nmore predictable than the present."},{"time":445799,"text":"And what it implies is a hundredfold multiplication"},{"time":450194,"text":"in the stock of information that is connected"},{"time":453167,"text":"via an I.P. address."},{"time":455395,"text":"Now, if the number of connections that we can make"},{"time":458856,"text":"is proportional to the number of pairs of data points,"},{"time":461996,"text":"a hundredfold multiplication in the quantity of data"},{"time":464459,"text":"is a ten-thousandfold multiplication"},{"time":466562,"text":"in the number of patterns"},{"time":468127,"text":"that we can see in that data,"},{"time":470204,"text":"this just in the last 10 or 11 years."},{"time":472864,"text":"This, I would submit, is a sea change,"},{"time":475688,"text":"a profound change in the economics"},{"time":477772,"text":"of the world that we live in."}]},{"cues":[{"time":479723,"text":"The first human genome,"},{"time":480887,"text":"that of James Watson,"},{"time":482453,"text":"was mapped as the culmination of the\nHuman Genome Project in the year 2000,"},{"time":486373,"text":"and it took about 200 million dollars"},{"time":488550,"text":"and about 10 years of work to map"},{"time":490531,"text":"just one person's genomic makeup."},{"time":492946,"text":"Since then, the costs of mapping\nthe genome have come down."},{"time":495551,"text":"In fact, they've come down in recent years"},{"time":497438,"text":"very dramatically indeed,"},{"time":499112,"text":"to the point where the cost \nis now below 1,000 dollars,"},{"time":501558,"text":"and it's confidently predicted that by the year 2015"},{"time":504509,"text":"it will be below 100 dollars --"},{"time":506240,"text":"a five or six order of magnitude drop"},{"time":509436,"text":"in the cost of genomic mapping"},{"time":511381,"text":"in just a 15-year period,"},{"time":513804,"text":"an extraordinary phenomenon."},{"time":516199,"text":"Now, in the days when mapping a genome"},{"time":520604,"text":"cost millions, or even tens of thousands,"},{"time":523613,"text":"it was basically a research enterprise."},{"time":525591,"text":"Scientists would gather some representative people,"},{"time":528133,"text":"and they would see patterns, and they would try"},{"time":529347,"text":"and make generalizations about\nhuman nature and disease"},{"time":532237,"text":"from the abstract patterns they find"},{"time":533828,"text":"from these particular selected individuals."},{"time":537288,"text":"But when the genome can \nbe mapped for 100 bucks,"},{"time":540121,"text":"99 dollars while you wait,"},{"time":542469,"text":"then what happens is, it becomes retail."},{"time":544659,"text":"It becomes above all clinical."},{"time":546516,"text":"You go the doctor with a cold,"},{"time":547728,"text":"and if he or she hasn't done it already,"},{"time":549662,"text":"the first thing they do is map your genome,"},{"time":551900,"text":"at which point what they're now doing"},{"time":553555,"text":"is not starting from some abstract \nknowledge of genomic medicine"},{"time":558084,"text":"and trying to work out how it applies to you,"},{"time":560148,"text":"but they're starting from your particular genome."},{"time":562717,"text":"Now think of the power of that."},{"time":564157,"text":"Think of where that takes us"},{"time":565946,"text":"when we can combine genomic data"},{"time":568892,"text":"with clinical data"},{"time":570381,"text":"with data about drug interactions"},{"time":572340,"text":"with the kind of ambient data that devices"},{"time":574629,"text":"like our phone and medical sensors"},{"time":576388,"text":"will increasingly be collecting."},{"time":578246,"text":"Think what happens when we collect all of that data"},{"time":580707,"text":"and we can put it together"},{"time":582180,"text":"in order to find patterns we wouldn't see before."},{"time":584668,"text":"This, I would suggest, perhaps it will take a while,"},{"time":587579,"text":"but this will drive a revolution in medicine."},{"time":590020,"text":"Fabulous, lots of people talk about this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":592340,"text":"But there's one thing that\ndoesn't get much attention."},{"time":594779,"text":"How is that model of colossal sharing"},{"time":598063,"text":"across all of those kinds of databases"},{"time":600709,"text":"compatible with the business models"},{"time":603201,"text":"of institutions and organizations and corporations"},{"time":605815,"text":"that are involved in this business today?"},{"time":608112,"text":"If your business is based on proprietary data,"},{"time":610888,"text":"if your competitive advantage\nis defined by your data,"},{"time":613931,"text":"how on Earth is that company or is that society"},{"time":617451,"text":"in fact going to achieve the value"},{"time":619549,"text":"that's implicit in the technology? They can't."}]},{"cues":[{"time":622554,"text":"So essentially what's happening here,"},{"time":624601,"text":"and genomics is merely one example of this,"},{"time":627245,"text":"is that technology is driving"},{"time":629559,"text":"the natural scaling of the activity"},{"time":632128,"text":"beyond the institutional boundaries within which"},{"time":635055,"text":"we have been used to thinking about it,"},{"time":637213,"text":"and in particular beyond the institutional boundaries"},{"time":639376,"text":"in terms of which business strategy"},{"time":641630,"text":"as a discipline is formulated."},{"time":645085,"text":"The basic story here is that what used to be"},{"time":648571,"text":"vertically integrated, oligopolistic competition"},{"time":652233,"text":"among essentially similar kinds of competitors"},{"time":655024,"text":"is evolving, by one means or another,"},{"time":657483,"text":"from a vertical structure to a horizontal one."},{"time":660844,"text":"Why is that happening?"},{"time":662559,"text":"It's happening because\ntransaction costs are plummeting"},{"time":665064,"text":"and because scale is polarizing."},{"time":666992,"text":"The plummeting of transaction costs"},{"time":668734,"text":"weakens the glue that holds value chains together,"},{"time":671372,"text":"and allows them to separate."},{"time":673040,"text":"The polarization of scale economies"},{"time":674975,"text":"towards the very small -- small is beautiful --"},{"time":678101,"text":"allows for scalable communities"},{"time":680769,"text":"to substitute for conventional corporate production."},{"time":683886,"text":"The scaling in the opposite direction,"},{"time":685890,"text":"towards things like big data,"},{"time":687923,"text":"drive the structure of business"},{"time":689332,"text":"towards the creation of new kinds of institutions"},{"time":692055,"text":"that can achieve that scale."},{"time":694033,"text":"But either way, the typically vertical structure"},{"time":696791,"text":"gets driven to becoming more horizontal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":699795,"text":"The logic isn't just about big data."},{"time":702210,"text":"If we were to look, for example,\nat the telecommunications industry,"},{"time":705536,"text":"you can tell the same story about fiber optics."},{"time":707911,"text":"If we look at the pharmaceutical industry,"},{"time":710047,"text":"or, for that matter, university research,"},{"time":711940,"text":"you can say exactly the same story"},{"time":713614,"text":"about so-called \"big science.\""},{"time":715353,"text":"And in the opposite direction,"},{"time":716888,"text":"if we look, say, at the energy sector,"},{"time":719085,"text":"where all the talk is about how households"},{"time":721945,"text":"will be efficient producers of green energy"},{"time":725529,"text":"and efficient conservers of energy,"},{"time":728157,"text":"that is, in fact, the reverse phenomenon."},{"time":730037,"text":"That is the fragmentation of scale"},{"time":731907,"text":"because the very small can substitute"},{"time":734261,"text":"for the traditional corporate scale."}]},{"cues":[{"time":736855,"text":"Either way, what we are driven to"},{"time":738646,"text":"is this horizontalization of the structure of industries,"},{"time":742017,"text":"and that implies fundamental changes"},{"time":744607,"text":"in how we think about strategy."},{"time":746669,"text":"It means, for example, that we need to think"},{"time":748701,"text":"about strategy as the curation"},{"time":751248,"text":"of these kinds of horizontal structure,"},{"time":753893,"text":"where things like business definition"},{"time":755533,"text":"and even industry definition"},{"time":757095,"text":"are actually the outcomes of strategy,"},{"time":759897,"text":"not something that the strategy presupposes."},{"time":763078,"text":"It means, for example, we need to work out"},{"time":766234,"text":"how to accommodate collaboration"},{"time":768591,"text":"and competition simultaneously."},{"time":770457,"text":"Think about the genome."},{"time":771543,"text":"We need to accommodate the very large"},{"time":773321,"text":"and the very small simultaneously."},{"time":775456,"text":"And we need industry structures"},{"time":777399,"text":"that will accommodate very,\nvery different motivations,"},{"time":780341,"text":"from the amateur motivations\nof people in communities"},{"time":782974,"text":"to maybe the social motivations"},{"time":784947,"text":"of infrastructure built by governments,"},{"time":787283,"text":"or, for that matter, cooperative institutions"},{"time":789908,"text":"built by companies that are otherwise competing,"},{"time":792400,"text":"because that is the only way\nthat they can get to scale."}]},{"cues":[{"time":795394,"text":"These kinds of transformations"},{"time":797371,"text":"render the traditional premises \nof business strategy obsolete."},{"time":801096,"text":"They drive us into a completely new world."},{"time":803665,"text":"They require us, whether we are"},{"time":805086,"text":"in the public sector or the private sector,"},{"time":807853,"text":"to think very fundamentally differently"},{"time":810153,"text":"about the structure of business,"},{"time":811973,"text":"and, at last, it makes strategy interesting again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":815427,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":818240,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}